<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-23T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="857" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d857">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14674.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-23T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Uninterrupted railway communication between Vera Cruz and Mexico City is
                            of utmost importance. Mexico City authorities have expressed willingness
                            to consider neutralization of Mexican Railways in order that passenger
                            and mail traffic may be resumed.<note n="21" xml:id="d857fn21">See
                                telegram of March 17 from the British Minister to Mexico.</note>
                            Take up with Carranza and point out that his favorable consideration of
                            plan would be universally approved.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>